    {
        "content": "<p>I have an image URI (e.g. <code>public://images/.../my-image.jpg</code>) but I need an image URL (e.g. <code>https://mydomain.com/files/images/.../my-image.jpg</code>). How do I convert one to the other?</p>",
        "id": 218248329,
        "sender_full_name": "BWPanda",
        "timestamp": 1606711269
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>backdrop_realpath()</code> provides the full path to the image on the server (e.g. <code>/var/www/...</code>)</p>",
        "id": 218248349,
        "sender_full_name": "BWPanda",
        "timestamp": 1606711315
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>url()</code> with <code>absolute =&gt; TRUE</code> outputs this weirdness: <code>https://mydomain.com/public%3A//images/...</code></p>",
        "id": 218248405,
        "sender_full_name": "BWPanda",
        "timestamp": 1606711375
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm sure there must be a function for this, I just can't find it...</p>",
        "id": 218248412,
        "sender_full_name": "BWPanda",
        "timestamp": 1606711408
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, found it: <a href=\"https://api.backdropcms.org/api/backdrop/core%21includes%21file.inc/function/file_create_url/1\">https://api.backdropcms.org/api/backdrop/core%21includes%21file.inc/function/file_create_url/1</a></p>",
